				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The reason I went with mv[np] target=source is because the 65xx processors don't have any other dual-operand instructions (addressing modes don't count; with saner mnemonics, they'd be + and not ,); and so it's ambiguous whether it's &quot;target,source&quot; (x86 style) or &quot;source,target&quot; (68k style). I preferred to just use = instead to make it unambiguous.<br /><br />However, you can easily extend bass in real-time with the traditional syntax if you like. See the manual for the &quot;arch.append&quot; syntax.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

